Immediate placement of an implant in a fresh extraction socket. This dental procedure where a tooth is removed, and an implant is inserted into the empty socket during the same appointment is often preferred when the tooth is non-restorable or needs extraction for other reasons.

The benefits of immediate implant placement include preserving bone and gum tissue, reducing the overall treatment time, and potentially providing better esthetic results. However, not all cases are suitable for immediate placement, and a thorough evaluation is necessary to determine if it's a viable option.
Implant specifications: JD Evolution Plus (6x10)

GUM TREATMENT
Photo-activated disinfection, also known as photodynamic therapy, represents a highly promising approach for managing chronic infections. In our field, it has demonstrated significant potential in enhancing the disinfection process during both surgical and non-surgical treatments for periodontitis. We recently published a study that utilized 635 nm wavelength light in conjunction with tolonium chloride for the management of periodontitis. Allow me to present a case study to illustrate this approach.
.
.
.
#periodontitis #gumhealth #dentistry #smile

This lecture was part of an International Online Educational Program organized by the Lasotronix company. 
In this lecture, I share a step by step procedure for a successful gingival depigmentation with the laser.

What are your thoughts on this approach? 

Although Laser-Assisted Periodontal Regeneration, also known as LANAP, is well-supported in the literature, it remains a controversial approach. Personally, I have witnessed positive results with my patients when employing this method for those who declined surgical interventions.

Here is a step-by-step protocol.

In this case, I used digital tools and tailored strategies to plan the implant procedure carefully, ensuring a personalized and effective approach for the best results. Implant planning is crucial in dentistry for precise treatment.
.

#DentalCare #PrecisionPlanning #periodontology #implants

This patient complained of severe gingival hyperplasia that did not improve even after scaling and root planing. Severe hyperplasia can be effectively managed using laser treatment when a strict protocol with specific parameters is followed, in addition to adhering to the gold standard of mechanical debridement.

➡️Full video available on YouTube: Marwan El Mobadder

Crafting confident smiles with precision: Another successful implant-supported denture case completed!

Implant-supported dentures on two implants for the lower arch offer sufficient stability and support while minimizing the number of implants needed. This approach balances functionality and cost-effectiveness, enhancing chewing efficiency and speech clarity without compromising on patient comfort.

🌟 #DentalCare #ImplantSuccess #SmileConfidence #implants
